    <div class="well">
        <h1>in this page you can see example usage of templates</h1>

        <div>
            <h2>example of "each block" template logic</h2>
            if an array is given with name "links" it will foreach and return the block count(array) number of times;<br>
            if this is associative array you can use {{key}} as array key and {{value}} as array value;<br>
            if this is indexed array you can use {{value}} and the {{key}} parameter will be the assigned index inside the array ;<br>
            if else parameter is given .. his content will be shown only when the list is empty;<br>
            if list is empty and there is no else param it will display empty string;<br>
            <br>
            example: associative gets array linksKeyValues
            <br>
            {{#each linksKeyValues}}
                <span>element #{{#number}} has index of {{#index}} in the array:</span><a href="{{value}}" > {{key}} </a><br>
            {{else}}
                <b>There are no links</b>
            {{/each}}
            <br>
            example: indexed gets array linksValues
            <br>
            {{#each linksValues}}
            <span>element #{{#number}} has index of {{#index}} in the array:</span><a href="{{value}}" > {{key}} </a><br>
            {{else}}
                <b>There are no links</b>
            {{/each}}
        </div>
        <hr>

        <div>
            <h2>example of unless template logic</h2>
            if variable with name "second" is given then it will check if its true or false <br>
            if it is false then will display the block <br>
            if it is true it will display an empty string <br>
            <br>
            example:
            <br>
            {{#unless unlessVariable}}
                unless the bool is true .. show this message!
            {{/unless}}
        </div>
        <hr>
        <h2>example of if template logic</h2>
        <div>
            if variable with name "first" is given then it will check if its true or false<br>
            if it is true then will display the block<br>
            if it is false it will display an empty string<br>
            <br>
            example:
            <br>
            {{#if ifVariable}}
                if true do this!
            {{/if}}
        </div>
        <hr>
        <div>
            <h2>example of if else template logic</h2>
            if variable with name "first" is given then it will check if its true or false <br>
            if it is true then will display the block from if to else<br>
            if it is false will display the else to end of the if<br>
            <br>
            example:
            <br>
            {{#if ifVariable}}
                if true do this!
            {{else}}
                else do this!
            {{/if}}
        </div>
        <hr>
        <div >
            <h2>how to display variables send from controller</h2>
            - if it is a string, int or float it will be displayed as string<br>
            - if the variable is type bool then will be converted to string true/false<br>
            - if it is an array it will be inplode() to string<br>
            <br>
            examples:
            <br>
            This is a string    => {#stringVariable}<br>
            This is a bool      => {#boolVariable}<br>
            This is an array    => {#arrayVariable}<br>
        </div>
        <hr>
    </div>
</div>
